  "prompt": "What are some of the funniest movies you've ever seen?",
  "response": "There are many comedies that have garnered a reputation for being particularly funny. Here are some classics and modern favorites across different styles of humor:\n\n1. **Airplane! (1980)** - A parody of disaster films, filled with puns and visual gags.\n2. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail (1975)** - A surreal take on the legend of King Arthur that features absurdity and clever wordplay.\n3. **The Big Lebowski (1998)** - A cult classic known for its quirky characters and offbeat humor.\n4. **Bridesmaids (2011)** - A fresh perspective on friendship and weddings with a perfect mix of raunchy and heartfelt moments.\n5. **Superbad (2007)** - A coming-of-age teen comedy that captures the awkwardness of high school friendships.\n6. **Groundhog Day (1993)** - A unique blend of romance and humor, featuring Bill Murray reliving the same day.\n7. **Step Brothers (2008)** - A ridiculous and hilarious exploration of adult immaturity and sibling rivalry.\n8. **Zoolander (2001)** - A satire of the fashion industry, led by Ben Stiller\u2019s iconic portrayal of a male model.\n9. **Shaun of the Dead (2004)** - A clever blend of horror and comedy that reinvigorates the zombie genre.\n10. **Tropic Thunder (2008)** - A satirical take on Hollywood and war films, featuring a star-studded cast and sharp humor.\n\nThese films offer a variety of comedic styles, from slapstick to clever satire, ensuring that there's something for everyone to enjoy!",
